subsection.p:
Since the strings are continuous at the junction the displacement of the string at the boundary at x=0 must be same whether we use \psi_1 or \psi_2 for the displacement at that point. Furthermore, the force on the know should be balanced. These two requirements give us boundary conditions relating \psi_1 and \psi_2. 

     \psi_1(0,t) = \psi_2(0,t)
     \left( \dfrac{\partial\psi_1(x,t)}{\partial x} \right)_{x=0}=  \left( \dfrac{\partial\psi_2(x,t)}{\partial x} \right)_{x=0}
